announcements.title: Retal Urban Development Company announces the signing of a development agreement with the National Housing Company (NHC) for a residential real estate project that includes commercial and mixed-use components, with a value of SAR 5.2 billion, located in Al-Fursan Suburb in Riyadh City.
Retal Urban Development Co. Announces Project Award from National Housing Company (NHC) with a value of 5.2 billion Saudi Riyals in Al Fursan Suburb in Riyadh
Retal Urban Development Co.  announces its Interim Financial results for the Period Ending on 2025-09-30 ( Nine Months )

Retal Urban Development Company announces the signing of a contract with Building Construction Limited Co. (A Subsidiary owned by 80%) to execute 901 residential units (villas) for the project owned by Jubail & Yanbu Industrial Cities Services Company (JABEEN), located in Jubail City, with a value of SAR 972 million, without any preferential conditions or advantages.

Retal Urban Development Company announces that one of its' subsidiaries (Building Construction Company Limited) signed a contract with ROSHN Group related to design and build a residential project consisting of multifamily buildings within SEDRA community with a value of SAR 461.9 million in Riyadh City.

text_sections.Company overview: The main activities of the company are as follows: The purchase and sale of lands, investment in real estate, its division, and the off-plan sales, general construction of buildings, non-residential public buildings constructions, including (schools, hospitals, hotels...etc).
text_sections.Company History: Retal Urban Development Company is a joint-stock Saudi company registered in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia under Commercial Registration No. 2051047761 corresponding to Al-Khobar on Rabi'' Al-Awal 12, 1433 corresponding to February 4, 2012. During the year 2020, the shareholders will convert the company from a limited liability company to a closed joint stock company. The company obtained a Ministerial approval on the announcement of the transformation on Muharram 9, 1442 (corresponding to August 28, 2020).On February 2, 2021, the General Assembly, at its meeting, approved the start of the procedures for listing the group in the stock market (Tadawul).
